From ba9ecdb51596ef0934bd51acfa09fcb6c09e190e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suharvest <suharvest@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 02:30:56 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] feat(qwen3-tts): backport Base speaker-encoder
 (external-embedding) path onto v0.8.0
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Base 0.6B conditions on an external speaker embedding (speaker_encoder /
reference audio), which v0.8.0 stripped in favor of CustomVoice named-speaker
tokens. Re-add the embedding path (passthrough milestone: embedding precomputed
offline and supplied as base64 LE float32; on-device speaker_encoder inference
is a follow-up):

- export.py: drop the CustomVoice-only export guard (warn instead) so Base
  Talker/CodePredictor/Code2Wav export via the checkpoint-agnostic pipeline.
  (speaker_encoder ONNX stage NOT grafted — v0.8 deleted audio_models/; deferred.)
- TalkerGenerationRequest: add std::vector<float> speakerEmbedding.
- talkerMLPKernels: assistantPreambleKernel row-6 uses external embedding when
  present (srcA=embedding, no ttsPad add), else CustomVoice embTable[speakerId].
  invokeAssistantPreamble gains trailing speakerEmbeddingPtr/hasSpeakerEmbedding
  (defaulted in header so the batched Thinker->Talker caller is unaffected).
- runtime: mSpeakerEmbeddingBuffer (fp16); projectToTalkerInput converts the
  float embedding -> half, uploads, and routes it to the preamble kernel.
- worker: base64Decode + base64ToFloatVec; parse speaker_embedding_b64 -> request.

Empty embedding = unchanged CustomVoice token path (backward compatible).

